ly assessed, due to the low statistics of the spectrum and to the observed\nenergy of the line, too close to the higher boundary of the Swift-XRT bandpass.\nHowever, our analysis suggests that, if the detection is confirmed, the line\ncould be associated with a high-velocity (vout~0.1c) outflow most likely\nlaunched within 80r_S. To our knowledge this is the first detection of a\npreviously unknown ultrafast wind with Swift. The high NH suggested by the\nobserved equivalent width of the line (EW~ -230eV, although with large\nuncertainties), would imply a kinetic output strong enough to be comparable to\nthe AGN bolometric luminosity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Jun 2015 09:22:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-16"}
